1
00:00:01,126 --> 00:00:06,507
[ MUSIC ]

2
00:00:06,507 --> 00:00:11,219
CAPTAIN'S LOG, STAR DATE 1312.4.

3
00:00:11,219 --> 00:00:12,847
THE IMPOSSIBLE HAS HAPPENED.

4
00:00:12,847 --> 00:00:14,473
FROM DIRECTLY AHEAD,
WE'RE PICKING UP

5
00:00:14,473 --> 00:00:16,350
A RECORDED DISTRESS SIGNAL,

6
00:00:16,350 --> 00:00:18,393
THE CALL LETTERS OF A VESSEL
WHICH HAS BEEN MISSING

7
00:00:18,393 --> 00:00:21,814
FOR OVER TWO CENTURIES.

8
00:00:21,814 --> 00:00:24,483
DID ANOTHER EARTH SHIP
ONCE PROBE OUT OF THE GALAXY

9
00:00:24,483 --> 00:00:26,401
AS WE INTEND TO DO?

10
00:00:26,401 --> 00:00:28,320
WHAT HAPPENED TO IT OUT THERE?

11
00:00:28,320 --> 00:00:32,240
IS THIS SOME WARNING
THEY'VE LEFT BEHIND?

12
00:00:32,240 --> 00:00:33,784
YOUR MOVE, CAPTAIN.

13
00:00:33,784 --> 00:00:35,744
WE SHOULD HAVE INTERCEPTED
BY NOW.

14
00:00:35,744 --> 00:00:37,997
THE BRIDGE SAID THEY'D CALL.

15
00:00:37,997 --> 00:00:41,000
I'LL HAVE YOU CHECKMATED
AT YOUR NEXT MOVE.

16
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:42,918
[ CHUCKLES ]

17
00:00:42,918 --> 00:00:45,796
HAVE I EVEN MENTIONED YOU PLAY
A VERY IRRITATING GAME OF CHESS,

18
00:00:45,796 --> 00:00:46,714
MR. SPOCK?

19
00:00:46,714 --> 00:00:48,340
IRRITATING.

20
00:00:48,340 --> 00:00:53,470
AH, YES.
ONE OF YOUR EARTH EMOTIONS.

21
00:00:58,141 --> 00:01:00,936
YOU'RE CERTAIN YOU DON'T KNOW
WHAT IRRITATION IS?

22
00:01:00,936 --> 00:01:03,939
THE FACT ONE OF MY ANCESTORS
MARRIED A HUMAN FEMALE.

23
00:01:03,939 --> 00:01:06,483
TERRIBLE HAVING BAD BLOOD
LIKE THAT.

24
00:01:06,483 --> 00:01:07,693
[ WHISTLE BLOWING ]

25
00:01:07,693 --> 00:01:08,777
Bridge to briefing lounge.

26
00:01:08,777 --> 00:01:11,488
OBJECT IS NOW WITHIN
TRACTOR BEAM RANGE.

27
00:01:11,488 --> 00:01:13,281
NO VISUAL CONTACT, MR. KELSO?

28
00:01:13,281 --> 00:01:15,951
NO, SIR.
IT'S TOO SMALL TO BE A VESSEL.

29
00:01:15,951 --> 00:01:18,871
IT ONLY READS ABOUT
ONE METER IN DIAMETER.

30
00:01:18,871 --> 00:01:20,789
NOT LARGE ENOUGH
EVEN FOR A LIFE BOAT.

31
00:01:20,789 --> 00:01:23,876
SMALL ENOUGH TO BRING IT ABOARD,
SIR, IF YOU WANNA RISK IT.

32
00:01:23,876 --> 00:01:26,503
LOCK ONTO IT, MR. KELSO.

33
00:01:26,503 --> 00:01:31,592
[ BEEPING ]

34
00:01:33,802 --> 00:01:35,387
MATERIAL LASER READY, SIR.

35
00:01:35,387 --> 00:01:36,889
BRING IT ABOARD.

36
00:01:36,889 --> 00:01:41,977
[ BEEPING ]

37
00:01:48,483 --> 00:01:51,486
OLD-STYLE SHIP RECORDER
THAT COULD BE EJECTED

38
00:01:51,486 --> 00:01:53,697
WHEN SOMETHING THREATENED
THE SHIP.

39
00:01:53,697 --> 00:01:55,866
MORE LIKE DESTROYED THE SHIP
IN THIS CASE.

40
00:01:55,866 --> 00:01:58,660
LOOK AT IT.
BURNT, PITTED.

41
00:01:58,660 --> 00:02:00,537
LET'S HOPE ITS TAPES ARE INTACT.

42
00:02:00,537 --> 00:02:02,790
WE'LL FEED IT
THROUGH MR. SPOCK'S COMPUTER.

43
00:02:02,790 --> 00:02:04,959
YES, SIR.

44
00:02:04,959 --> 00:02:09,004
[ BEEPING ]

45
00:02:09,004 --> 00:02:12,716
IT'S BEGUN TRANSMITTING, SIR.

46
00:02:12,716 --> 00:02:15,803
FLASH THE BRIDGE!
PUT ALL DECKS ON THE ALERT!

47
00:02:15,803 --> 00:02:19,056
[ SIREN ]

48
00:02:19,056 --> 00:02:24,144
[ MUSIC ]

49
00:02:25,938 --> 00:02:30,776
[ MUSIC ]

50
00:02:30,776 --> 00:02:34,696
SPACE, THE FINAL FRONTIER.

51
00:02:34,696 --> 00:02:38,575
THESE ARE THE VOYAGES
OF THE STARSHIP<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

52
00:02:38,575 --> 00:02:43,413
ITS FIVE-YEAR MISSION:
TO EXPLORE STRANGE NEW WORLDS,

53
00:02:43,413 --> 00:02:47,459
TO SEEK OUT NEW LIFE
AND NEW CIVILIZATIONS,

54
00:02:47,459 --> 00:02:51,505
TO BOLDLY GO
WHERE NO MAN HAS GONE BEFORE.

55
00:02:51,505 --> 00:02:56,593
[ MUSIC ]

56
00:03:16,530 --> 00:03:21,618
[ MUSIC ]

57
00:03:23,704 --> 00:03:28,792
[ SIREN ]

58
00:03:33,047 --> 00:03:34,213
HOLD IT, JIM.

59
00:03:34,213 --> 00:03:35,215
GETTING INTO SHAPE?

60
00:03:35,215 --> 00:03:36,925
YEAH. WELL, I FIGURED
YOU WEREN'T ON THE BRIDGE.

61
00:03:36,925 --> 00:03:40,261
KELSO'S VOICE SOUNDED
A LITTLE NERVOUS.

62
00:03:40,261 --> 00:03:42,389
WELL, UH, YOU FINISHED THE GAME?

63
00:03:42,389 --> 00:03:44,641
MMM. HE PLAYED MOST ILLOGICALLY.

64
00:03:44,641 --> 00:03:49,813
HIS NEXT MOVE SHOULD HAVE BEEN
THE ROOK.

65
00:03:53,775 --> 00:03:55,443
YOU'RE RELIEVED, MR. ALDEN.

66
00:03:55,443 --> 00:04:00,908
ACKNOWLEDGED, MR. MITCHELL.

67
00:04:00,908 --> 00:04:05,286
SCREEN ON.

68
00:04:05,286 --> 00:04:10,458
SCREEN ON, SIR.

69
00:04:10,458 --> 00:04:15,547
[ FAINT BEEPING ]

70
00:04:17,049 --> 00:04:18,717
APPROACHING GALAXY EDGE, SIR.

71
00:04:18,717 --> 00:04:23,889
NEUTRALIZE WARP, MR. MITCHELL.
HOLD THIS POSITION.

72
00:04:29,853 --> 00:04:31,939
NEUTRALIZED WARP, SIR.

73
00:04:31,939 --> 00:04:34,233
ADDRESS INTERCRAFT.

74
00:04:34,233 --> 00:04:35,442
INTERCRAFT OPEN.

75
00:04:35,442 --> 00:04:37,152
THIS IS THE CAPTAIN SPEAKING.

76
00:04:37,152 --> 00:04:39,696
THE OBJECT WE ENCOUNTERED
IS A SHIP'S DISASTER RECORDER

77
00:04:39,696 --> 00:04:41,615
APPARENTLY EJECTED
FROM THE SS<i> VALIANT</i>

78
00:04:41,615 --> 00:04:42,991
ALMOST 200 YEARS AGO.

79
00:04:42,991 --> 00:04:46,078
TAPES ARE BURNT OUT.
TRYING THE MEMORY BANKS.

80
00:04:46,078 --> 00:04:47,370
WE HOPE TO LEARN
FROM THE RECORDER

81
00:04:47,370 --> 00:04:51,583
WHAT THE<i> VALIANT</i> WAS DOING HERE
AND WHAT DESTROYED THE VESSEL.

82
00:04:51,583 --> 00:04:52,876
WE'LL MOVE OUT INTO OUR PROBE

83
00:04:52,876 --> 00:04:54,253
AS SOON AS WE HAVE
THOSE ANSWERS.

84
00:04:54,253 --> 00:04:55,545
ALL DECKS, STAND BY.

85
00:04:55,545 --> 00:04:56,588
OUR DEPARTMENT HEADS, SIR.

86
00:04:56,588 --> 00:04:57,798
YOU WANTED EVERYBODY
ON THE BRIDGE

87
00:04:57,798 --> 00:05:01,051
BEFORE WE LEFT THE GALAXY.

88
00:05:01,051 --> 00:05:02,052
JONES.

89
00:05:02,052 --> 00:05:05,639
THE NAME'S SMITH, SIR.

90
00:05:05,639 --> 00:05:07,307
ASTRO SCIENCES STANDING BY,
CAPTAIN.

91
00:05:07,307 --> 00:05:10,060
ENGINEERING DIVISION READY,
AS ALWAYS.

92
00:05:10,060 --> 00:05:11,686
LIFE SCIENCES READY, SIR.

93
00:05:11,686 --> 00:05:13,855
THIS IS DR. DEHNER
WHO JOINED THE SHIP

94
00:05:13,855 --> 00:05:15,356
AT THE ALDEBARAN COLONY.

95
00:05:15,356 --> 00:05:16,357
PSYCHIATRY, CAPTAIN.

96
00:05:16,357 --> 00:05:18,152
MY ASSIGNMENT
IS TO STUDY CREW REACTION

97
00:05:18,152 --> 00:05:19,569
IN EMERGENCY CONDITIONS.

98
00:05:19,569 --> 00:05:24,324
GETTING SOMETHING
FROM THE RECORDER NOW.

99
00:05:24,324 --> 00:05:26,952
IF THERE WAS AN EMERGENCY,
I'D BE INTERESTED

100
00:05:26,952 --> 00:05:29,788
IN HOW THAT CREW REACTED, TOO.

101
00:05:29,788 --> 00:05:33,583
WELL, IMPROVING THE BREED,
DOCTOR, IS THAT YOUR LINE?

102
00:05:33,583 --> 00:05:36,044
I HEARD THAT'S MORE
YOUR SPECIALTY, COMMANDER,

103
00:05:36,044 --> 00:05:41,508
LINE INCLUDED.

104
00:05:41,508 --> 00:05:43,135
WALKING FREEZER UNIT.

105
00:05:43,135 --> 00:05:47,264
DECODING MEMORY BANKS.
I'LL TRY TO INTERPOLATE.

106
00:05:47,264 --> 00:05:49,224
THE<i> VALIANT</i> HAD ENCOUNTERED
A MAGNETIC SPACE STORM

107
00:05:49,224 --> 00:05:50,976
AND WAS BEING SWEPT
IN THIS DIRECTION.

108
00:05:50,976 --> 00:05:53,312
THE OLD IMPULSE ENGINES
WEREN'T STRONG ENOUGH.

109
00:05:53,312 --> 00:05:55,939
SWEPT PAST THIS POINT,
ABOUT A HALF LIGHT-YEAR

110
00:05:55,939 --> 00:05:57,274
OUT OF THE GALAXY.

111
00:05:57,274 --> 00:05:59,818
THEY WERE THROWN CLEAR,
TURNED AND HEADED BACK

112
00:05:59,818 --> 00:06:02,737
INTO THE GALAXY HERE.

113
00:06:02,737 --> 00:06:03,655
I'M NOT GETTING IT ALL.

114
00:06:03,655 --> 00:06:05,490
THE TAPES
ARE PRETTY BADLY BURNED.

115
00:06:05,490 --> 00:06:08,035
SOUNDS LIKE THE SHIP
HAD ENCOUNTERED

116
00:06:08,035 --> 00:06:14,082
SOME UNKNOWN FORCE.

117
00:06:14,082 --> 00:06:17,669
NOW, ORDERS, COUNTER ORDERS.

118
00:06:17,669 --> 00:06:19,713
REPEATED URGENT REQUESTS
FOR INFORMATION

119
00:06:19,713 --> 00:06:23,300
FROM THE SHIP'S COMPUTER RECORDS
FOR ANYTHING CONCERNING ESP

120
00:06:23,300 --> 00:06:24,592
IN HUMAN BEINGS.

121
00:06:24,592 --> 00:06:27,637
EXTRASENSORY PERCEPTION?

122
00:06:27,637 --> 00:06:31,183
DR. DEHNER, HOW ARE YOU ON ESP?

123
00:06:31,183 --> 00:06:34,061
IN TESTS I'VE TAKEN,
MY ESP RATED RATHER HIGH.

124
00:06:34,061 --> 00:06:36,771
I'M ASKING WHAT YOU KNOW
ABOUT ESP.

125
00:06:36,771 --> 00:06:40,192
IT IS A FACT THAT SOME PEOPLE
CAN SENSE FUTURE HAPPENINGS,

126
00:06:40,192 --> 00:06:42,610
READ THE BACKS OF PLAYING CARDS
AND SO ON.

127
00:06:42,610 --> 00:06:45,446
BUT THE ESPER CAPACITY
IS ALWAYS QUITE LIMITED.

128
00:06:45,446 --> 00:06:50,202
SEVERE DAMAGE.
SEVEN CREWMEN DEAD.

129
00:06:50,202 --> 00:06:52,579
NO, MAKE THAT SIX.

130
00:06:52,579 --> 00:06:54,748
ONE CREWMAN SEEMED
TO HAVE RECOVERED.

131
00:06:54,748 --> 00:06:56,208
THAT'S WHEN THEY BECAME
INTERESTED

132
00:06:56,208 --> 00:06:59,294
IN EXTRASENSORY PERCEPTION.

133
00:06:59,294 --> 00:07:03,382
MORE THAN INTERESTED,
ALMOST FRANTIC ABOUT IT.

134
00:07:03,382 --> 00:07:04,632
[ FREQUENCY DISTORTION ]

135
00:07:04,632 --> 00:07:08,095
NO, THIS--THIS MUST BE GARBLED.

136
00:07:08,095 --> 00:07:13,267
I GET SOMETHING ABOUT DESTRUCT.

137
00:07:13,267 --> 00:07:14,184
I MUST HAVE READ IT WRONG.

138
00:07:14,184 --> 00:07:15,727
IT SOUNDED LIKE THE CAPTAIN
GIVING AN ORDER

139
00:07:15,727 --> 00:07:18,730
TO DESTROY HIS OWN SHIP.

140
00:07:18,730 --> 00:07:23,777
[ MUSIC ]

141
00:07:29,950 --> 00:07:31,743
COMMENTS?

142
00:07:31,743 --> 00:07:34,413
THE ONLY FACT WE HAVE FOR SURE
IS THAT THE SS<i> VALIANT</i>

143
00:07:34,413 --> 00:07:37,874
WAS DESTROYED.

144
00:07:37,874 --> 00:07:39,376
THAT'S PROBABLY
THE BEST ARGUMENT

145
00:07:39,376 --> 00:07:40,835
TO CONTINUE THE PROBE.

146
00:07:40,835 --> 00:07:42,712
OTHER VESSELS WILL BE HEADING
OUT HERE SOMEDAY,

147
00:07:42,712 --> 00:07:44,631
AND THEY'LL HAVE TO KNOW
WHAT THEY'LL BE FACING.

148
00:07:44,631 --> 00:07:48,093
WE'RE LEAVING THE GALAXY,
MR. MITCHELL.

149
00:07:48,093 --> 00:07:50,429
AHEAD, WARP FACTOR ONE.

150
00:07:50,429 --> 00:07:55,516
[ BEEPS ]

151
00:07:57,269 --> 00:08:02,316
[ MUSIC ]

152
00:08:14,077 --> 00:08:15,578
FORCE FIELD OF SOME KIND.

153
00:08:15,578 --> 00:08:20,708
WE'RE COMING UP ON IT FAST.

154
00:08:24,171 --> 00:08:26,006
SENSOR BEAM ON.

155
00:08:26,006 --> 00:08:27,841
SENSOR BEAM ON, SIR.

156
00:08:27,841 --> 00:08:29,884
DEFLECTORS FULL INTENSITY.

157
00:08:29,884 --> 00:08:35,598
DEFLECTORS FULL INTENSITY.

158
00:08:35,598 --> 00:08:37,684
DEFLECTORS SAY
THERE'S SOMETHING THERE.

159
00:08:37,684 --> 00:08:39,602
SENSORS SAY THERE ISN'T.

160
00:08:39,602 --> 00:08:44,107
DENSITY NEGATIVE.
RADIATION NEGATIVE.

161
00:08:44,107 --> 00:08:46,485
ENERGY NEGATIVE.

162
00:08:46,485 --> 00:08:53,033
WHATEVER IT IS,
CONTACT IN 12 SECONDS.

163
00:08:53,033 --> 00:08:58,121
[ MUSIC ]

164
00:09:25,106 --> 00:09:32,072
GRAVITATION ON AUTOMATIC.

165
00:09:32,072 --> 00:09:34,074
[ EXPLOSIONS ]

166
00:09:34,074 --> 00:09:38,078
EMERGENCY STATIONS.
ALL DECKS ON FIRE ALERT.

167
00:09:38,078 --> 00:09:39,954
NEUTRALIZE CONTROLS.

168
00:09:39,954 --> 00:09:45,377
KELSO, PUT IT ON MANUAL.

169
00:09:45,377 --> 00:09:46,669
ANY RADIATION? ANYTHING?

170
00:09:46,669 --> 00:09:49,464
NEGATIVE!

171
00:09:49,464 --> 00:09:54,553
HELMSMAN, TAKE US OUT OF HERE!

172
00:10:01,226 --> 00:10:04,104
HELMSMAN!

173
00:10:04,104 --> 00:10:09,192
LATERAL POWER!

174
00:10:23,664 --> 00:10:25,250
TAKE DAMAGE REPORTS.

175
00:10:25,250 --> 00:10:27,335
DAMAGE CONTROL REPORTS,
ALL STATIONS!

176
00:10:27,335 --> 00:10:31,214
Gravity control
switching to battery.

177
00:10:31,214 --> 00:10:38,805
SOMETHING HIT ME,
LIKE AN ELECTRICAL CHARGE.

178
00:10:38,805 --> 00:10:41,099
HE'S ALIVE.
APPEARS TO BE IN SHOCK.

179
00:10:41,099 --> 00:10:43,768
Engineering Deck Three,
can you give damage report?

180
00:10:43,768 --> 00:10:46,396
The sensor beams.
Full power on the deflectors.

181
00:10:46,396 --> 00:10:48,815
MAIN ENGINES ARE OUT, SIR.
WE'RE ON EMERGENCY POWER CELLS.

182
00:10:48,815 --> 00:10:50,191
CASUALTIES, NINE DEAD.

183
00:10:50,191 --> 00:10:52,193
Gravity is down to .8.

184
00:10:52,193 --> 00:10:53,903
All decks,
this is Bridge engineering.

185
00:10:53,903 --> 00:10:55,822
Due to the emergency
conditions...

186
00:10:55,822 --> 00:11:02,579
GARY. GARY, ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

187
00:11:02,579 --> 00:11:04,289
I'M A LITTLE WEAK
FOR SOME REASON, JIM,

188
00:11:04,289 --> 00:11:09,085
BUT I FEEL ALL RIGHT NOW.

189
00:11:09,085 --> 00:11:14,174
[ MUSIC ]

190
00:11:17,760 --> 00:11:22,765
CAPTAIN'S LOG, STAR DATE 1312.9.

191
00:11:22,765 --> 00:11:27,770
SHIP'S CONDITION, HEADING BACK
ON IMPULSE POWER ONLY.

192
00:11:27,770 --> 00:11:29,648
MAIN ENGINES BURNED OUT.

193
00:11:29,648 --> 00:11:32,691
THE SHIP'S SPACE WARP ABILITY:
GONE.

194
00:11:32,691 --> 00:11:34,693
EARTH BASES
WHICH WERE ONLY DAYS AWAY

195
00:11:34,693 --> 00:11:39,991
ARE NOW YEARS IN THE DISTANCE.

196
00:11:39,991 --> 00:11:45,580
OUR OVERRIDING QUESTION NOW IS
WHAT DESTROYED THE<i> VALIANT?</i>

197
00:11:45,580 --> 00:11:48,500
THEY LIVED THROUGH THE BARRIER,
JUST AS WE HAVE.

198
00:11:48,500 --> 00:11:52,504
WHAT HAPPENED TO THEM
AFTER THAT?

199
00:11:52,504 --> 00:11:57,592
[ MUSIC ]

200
00:12:02,305 --> 00:12:05,141
[ FREQUENCY BEEPING ]

201
00:12:05,141 --> 00:12:07,726
AUTOPSY REPORT, SIR.

202
00:12:07,726 --> 00:12:10,355
EACH CASE SHOWED DAMAGE
TO THE BODY'S NEURAL CIRCUIT.

203
00:12:10,355 --> 00:12:12,148
AN AREA OF THE BRAIN
WAS BURNED OUT.

204
00:12:12,148 --> 00:12:13,400
AND YOU,
ARE YOU FEELING ALL RIGHT?

205
00:12:13,400 --> 00:12:17,028
YES. MITCHELL, TOO,
EXCEPT FOR HIS EYES.

206
00:12:17,028 --> 00:12:19,738
WE'RE TRYING TO FIND A REASON
FOR THAT NOW,

207
00:12:19,738 --> 00:12:21,949
AND WHY, OUT OF OUR WHOLE CREW,
ONLY CERTAIN PEOPLE

208
00:12:21,949 --> 00:12:22,909
WERE AFFECTED.

209
00:12:22,909 --> 00:12:24,578
I THINK WE'VE FOUND THAT ANSWER,
DOCTOR.

210
00:12:24,578 --> 00:12:26,871
YOU MENTIONED THAT TESTS SHOW
THAT YOU HAVE A HIGH DEGREE

211
00:12:26,871 --> 00:12:29,082
OF EXTRASENSORY PERCEPTION.

212
00:12:29,082 --> 00:12:30,749
SO DO THE RECORDS OF THE OTHERS.

213
00:12:30,749 --> 00:12:32,919
GARY MITCHELL HAS THE HIGHEST
ESPER RATING OF ALL.

214
00:12:32,919 --> 00:12:34,879
IF YOU'RE SUGGESTING
THERE'S ANYTHING DANGEROUS--

215
00:12:34,879 --> 00:12:36,423
BEFORE THE<i> VALIANT</i>
WAS DESTROYED,

216
00:12:36,423 --> 00:12:38,007
ITS CAPTAIN
WAS FRANTICALLY SEARCHING

217
00:12:38,007 --> 00:12:40,218
FOR ESP INFORMATION ON HIS CREW.

218
00:12:40,218 --> 00:12:44,055
ESPERS ARE SIMPLY PEOPLE
WITH FLASHES OF INSIGHT.

219
00:12:44,055 --> 00:12:45,056
ARE THERE NOT ALSO THOSE

220
00:12:45,056 --> 00:12:47,267
WHO SEEM TO SEE
THROUGH SOLID OBJECTS,

221
00:12:47,267 --> 00:12:49,561
CAUSE FIRES TO START
SPONTANEOUSLY?

222
00:12:49,561 --> 00:12:51,145
THERE'S NOTHING ABOUT IT
THAT COULD POSSIBLY MAKE

223
00:12:51,145 --> 00:12:53,314
A PERSON DANGEROUS.

224
00:12:53,314 --> 00:12:56,192
DR. DEHNER IS SPEAKING
OF NORMAL ESP POWER.

225
00:12:56,192 --> 00:12:57,736
PERHAPS YOU KNOW
OF ANOTHER KIND?

226
00:12:57,736 --> 00:13:03,742
DO WE KNOW FOR SURE, DOCTOR,
THAT THERE ISN'T ANOTHER KIND?

227
00:13:03,742 --> 00:13:08,829
[ MUSIC ]

228
00:13:40,361 --> 00:13:46,743
HELLO, JIM.

229
00:13:46,743 --> 00:13:49,162
HEY, YOU LOOK WORRIED.

230
00:13:49,162 --> 00:13:50,789
I'VE BEEN WORRIED ABOUT YOU
EVER SINCE THAT NIGHT

231
00:13:50,789 --> 00:13:51,872
ON DENEB IV.

232
00:13:51,872 --> 00:13:54,125
[ CHUCKLES ]

233
00:13:54,125 --> 00:13:56,628
YEAH, SHE WAS NOVA, THAT ONE.

234
00:13:56,628 --> 00:13:59,172
NOT NEARLY AS MANY AFTER-EFFECTS
THIS TIME,

235
00:13:59,172 --> 00:13:59,964
EXCEPT FOR THE EYES.

236
00:13:59,964 --> 00:14:03,802
THEY KIND OF STARE BACK AT ME
WHEN I'M SHAVING.

237
00:14:03,802 --> 00:14:06,095
DO YOU FEEL ANY DIFFERENT?

238
00:14:06,095 --> 00:14:08,348
IN A WAY, I FEEL BETTER
THAN I'VE EVER FELT BEFORE

239
00:14:08,348 --> 00:14:10,433
IN MY LIFE.

240
00:14:10,433 --> 00:14:13,144
IT ACTUALLY SEEMS
TO HAVE DONE ME SOME GOOD.

241
00:14:13,144 --> 00:14:14,604
HOW?

242
00:14:14,604 --> 00:14:16,397
WELL, I'M GETTING A CHANCE
TO READ

243
00:14:16,397 --> 00:14:20,694
SOME OF THAT LONGHAIR STUFF
YOU LIKE.

244
00:14:20,694 --> 00:14:22,821
[ CHUCKLES ]

245
00:14:22,821 --> 00:14:25,365
HEY, MAN, I REMEMBER YOU
BACK AT THE ACADEMY.

246
00:14:25,365 --> 00:14:27,784
A STACK OF BOOKS WITH LEGS.

247
00:14:27,784 --> 00:14:30,077
THE FIRST THING I EVER HEARD
FROM AN UPPERCLASSMEN WAS,

248
00:14:30,077 --> 00:14:31,705
"WATCH OUT FOR LIEUTENANT KIRK.

249
00:14:31,705 --> 00:14:35,082
IN HIS CLASS,
YOU EITHER THINK OR SINK."

250
00:14:35,082 --> 00:14:37,168
[ CHUCKLES ]

251
00:14:37,168 --> 00:14:38,919
I WASN'T THAT BAD, WAS I?

252
00:14:38,919 --> 00:14:42,590
IF I HADN'T AIMED THAT LITTLE
BLONDE LAB TECHNICIAN AT YOU...

253
00:14:42,590 --> 00:14:45,760
YOU WHAT?
Y-YOU PLANNED THAT?

254
00:14:45,760 --> 00:14:50,431
WELL, YOU WANTED ME TO THINK,
DIDN'T YOU?

255
00:14:50,431 --> 00:14:53,059
I OUTLINED HER WHOLE CAMPAIGN
FOR HER.

256
00:14:53,059 --> 00:14:55,687
I ALMOST MARRIED HER!

257
00:14:55,687 --> 00:14:58,815
YOU BETTER BE GOOD TO ME.

258
00:14:58,815 --> 00:15:03,944
I'M GETTING EVEN BETTER IDEAS
HERE.

259
00:15:07,240 --> 00:15:08,742
[ CHUCKLES ]

260
00:15:08,742 --> 00:15:12,829
YOU? SPINOZA?

261
00:15:12,829 --> 00:15:14,748
ONCE YOU GET INTO HIM,
HE'S RATHER SIMPLE THOUGH.

262
00:15:14,748 --> 00:15:16,541
CHILDISH, ALMOST.

263
00:15:16,541 --> 00:15:19,085
I DON'T AGREE WITH HIM AT ALL.

264
00:15:19,085 --> 00:15:20,002
GO ON.

265
00:15:20,002 --> 00:15:23,089
HEY, I'M TRYING TO TELL YOU
I FEEL FINE.

266
00:15:23,089 --> 00:15:26,843
WHEN DO I GO BACK ON DUTY?

267
00:15:26,843 --> 00:15:29,763
I'M GONNA ASK DR. DEHNER
TO KEEP YOU UNDER OBSERVATION

268
00:15:29,763 --> 00:15:32,223
FOR A WHILE.

269
00:15:32,223 --> 00:15:33,558
WITH ALMOST A HUNDRED WOMEN
ONBOARD,

270
00:15:33,558 --> 00:15:36,895
YOU CAN DO BETTER THAN THAT,
FRIEND CAPTAIN.

271
00:15:36,895 --> 00:15:41,274
CONSIDER IT A CHALLENGE.

272
00:15:41,274 --> 00:15:45,111
THAT DOESN'T SEEM VERY FRIENDLY.

273
00:15:45,111 --> 00:15:52,452
DIDN'T I SAY
YOU'D BETTER BE GOOD TO ME?

274
00:15:52,452 --> 00:15:57,540
[ MUSIC ]

275
00:16:01,127 --> 00:16:06,215
[ CLICKING ]

276
00:16:16,392 --> 00:16:21,606
HE'S READING EVEN FASTER NOW
THAN JUST A FEW MOMENTS AGO.

277
00:16:21,606 --> 00:16:26,778
IS THAT GARY MITCHELL,
THE ONE YOU USED TO KNOW?

278
00:16:29,363 --> 00:16:32,074
PUT A 24-HOUR WATCH
ON THE SICKBAY.

279
00:16:32,074 --> 00:16:37,246
FULLEST POSSIBLE RANGE
OF EXAMINATIONS AND TESTS.

280
00:16:40,458 --> 00:16:45,546
[ MUSIC ]

281
00:16:53,095 --> 00:16:57,976
PERFECT, PERFECT.

282
00:16:57,976 --> 00:17:00,436
I'VE NEVER HAD A PATIENT
LIKE YOU, GARY.

283
00:17:00,436 --> 00:17:02,313
EVEN THE HEALTHIEST
ARE GENERALLY OFF

284
00:17:02,313 --> 00:17:07,360
ON SOME READING.

285
00:17:11,489 --> 00:17:13,992
I KNOW YOU DON'T PARTICULARLY
LIKE ME, MR. MITCHELL,

286
00:17:13,992 --> 00:17:17,286
BUT SINCE I AM ASSIGNED HERE,
CAN WE MAKE THE BEST OF IT?

287
00:17:17,286 --> 00:17:18,037
[ SMIRKS ]

288
00:17:18,037 --> 00:17:19,747
I'VE GOT NOTHING AGAINST YOU,
DOCTOR.

289
00:17:19,747 --> 00:17:24,043
NOR AGAINST THE WALKING
FREEZER UNIT?

290
00:17:24,043 --> 00:17:28,715
WELL, I--SORRY ABOUT THAT.

291
00:17:28,715 --> 00:17:32,844
WOMEN PROFESSIONALS
DO TEND TO OVERCOMPENSATE.

292
00:17:32,844 --> 00:17:36,180
NOW, LET'S TALK ABOUT YOU.
HOW DO YOU FEEL?

293
00:17:36,180 --> 00:17:39,225
YOU KNOW, EVERYBODY,
EVERYBODY SEEMS WORRIED

294
00:17:39,225 --> 00:17:42,562
THAT I DON'T HAVE SOME KIND
OF A FEVER OR SOMETHING.

295
00:17:42,562 --> 00:17:44,438
[ SMIRKS ]

296
00:17:44,438 --> 00:17:49,610
MAYBE IF WE COULD JUST CHANGE
THESE DIALS--

297
00:17:55,033 --> 00:17:59,913
NOW, BACK TO NORMAL, I THINK.

298
00:17:59,913 --> 00:18:05,001
HOW DID YOU DO THAT?

299
00:18:07,336 --> 00:18:12,425
I'M NOT SURE, I--

300
00:18:12,425 --> 00:18:14,677
I JUST THOUGHT OF
MAKING IT HAPPEN, AND IT DOES.

301
00:18:14,677 --> 00:18:20,391
IT'S--

302
00:18:20,391 --> 00:18:22,351
HEY--

303
00:18:22,351 --> 00:18:27,440
HEY, WATCH THIS, DOC.

304
00:18:41,079 --> 00:18:47,835
STOP IT. STOP IT!

305
00:18:47,835 --> 00:18:49,587
YOU WERE DEAD
FOR ALMOST 22 SECONDS.

306
00:18:49,587 --> 00:18:52,381
THERE WERE NO READINGS AT ALL.

307
00:18:52,381 --> 00:18:58,471
YEAH.

308
00:18:58,471 --> 00:19:01,682
OH, BOY.

309
00:19:01,682 --> 00:19:05,937
YOU, YOU KNOW, DOC,
THERE HAVE BEEN OTHER THINGS,

310
00:19:05,937 --> 00:19:09,148
TOO, LIKE, LIKE, GOING HALFWAY
THROUGH THE SHIP'S LIBRARY

311
00:19:09,148 --> 00:19:11,818
IN HARDLY A DAY.

312
00:19:11,818 --> 00:19:16,363
YEAH.

313
00:19:16,363 --> 00:19:21,661
OH, WHAT'S HAPPENING TO ME?

314
00:19:21,661 --> 00:19:24,330
DO YOU REMEMBER EVERYTHING
YOU READ THAT QUICKLY?

315
00:19:24,330 --> 00:19:26,082
YEAH.

316
00:19:26,082 --> 00:19:28,584
ON ANY TAPE?

317
00:19:28,584 --> 00:19:33,673
SURE. YEAH.

318
00:19:36,467 --> 00:19:40,680
TRY THIS ONE.

319
00:19:40,680 --> 00:19:43,016
YEAH.

320
00:19:43,016 --> 00:19:49,563
PAGE 387.

321
00:19:49,563 --> 00:19:52,441
"MY LOVE HAS WINGS.

322
00:19:52,441 --> 00:19:55,945
"SLENDER, FEATHERED THINGS
WITH GRACE IN UPSWEPT CURVE

323
00:19:55,945 --> 00:19:58,238
AND TAPERED TIP."

324
00:19:58,238 --> 00:20:02,493
NIGHTINGALE WOMAN,
WRITTEN BY, BY TARBOLDE

325
00:20:02,493 --> 00:20:05,830
ON THE CANOPIUS PLANET
BACK IN 1996.

326
00:20:05,830 --> 00:20:09,625
IT'S FUNNY YOU PICKED THAT ONE,
DOCTOR.

327
00:20:09,625 --> 00:20:15,297
WHY?

328
00:20:15,297 --> 00:20:17,424
THAT'S ONE OF THE MOST
PASSIONATE LOVE SONNETS

329
00:20:17,424 --> 00:20:22,471
OF THE PAST COUPLE OF CENTURIES.

330
00:20:24,932 --> 00:20:29,896
HOW DO YOU FEEL, DOCTOR?

331
00:20:29,896 --> 00:20:33,900
-WHAT?
-HOW DO YOU FEEL?

332
00:20:33,900 --> 00:20:35,735
I JUST FELL. NOTHING HAPPENED.

333
00:20:35,735 --> 00:20:41,074
NO? ARE YOU SURE?

334
00:20:41,074 --> 00:20:44,410
ARE YOU SURE?

335
00:20:49,498 --> 00:20:52,710
I WAS ON MY COFFEE BREAK.
I THOUGHT I'D CHECK UP ON YOU.

336
00:20:52,710 --> 00:20:54,587
YEAH.

337
00:20:54,587 --> 00:20:59,717
THAT'S OKAY, LEE. COME ON IN.

338
00:20:59,717 --> 00:21:01,427
DON'T LET THE LIGHT IN MY EYES
BOTHER YOU, PAL.

339
00:21:01,427 --> 00:21:06,348
IT'S ALL FOR OUR, OUR
GOOD-LOOKING LADY DOCTOR HERE.

340
00:21:06,348 --> 00:21:07,225
[ CHUCKLES ]

341
00:21:07,225 --> 00:21:08,475
YEAH. SURE.

342
00:21:08,475 --> 00:21:11,687
SO, UH, SO, HOW GO THE REPAIRS?

343
00:21:11,687 --> 00:21:14,648
WELL, THE MAIN ENGINES ARE GONE,

344
00:21:14,648 --> 00:21:18,360
UNLESS WE CAN FIND SOME WAY
TO RE-ENERGIZE THEM.

345
00:21:18,360 --> 00:21:20,113
YOU'D BETTER CHECK
THE STARBOARD IMPULSE PACKS.

346
00:21:20,113 --> 00:21:22,448
THOSE POINTS HAVE ABOUT DECAYED
TO LEAD.

347
00:21:22,448 --> 00:21:24,324
OH, YEAH, SURE, MITCH.

348
00:21:24,324 --> 00:21:27,286
I'M NOT JOKING, LEE!

349
00:21:27,286 --> 00:21:28,370
YOU ACTIVATE THOSE PACKS,

350
00:21:28,370 --> 00:21:31,958
AND YOU'LL BLOW
THE WHOLE IMPULSE DECK.

351
00:21:31,958 --> 00:21:35,419
I'LL GET ON IT RIGHT AWAY.

352
00:21:35,419 --> 00:21:38,672
I JUST WANTED TO STOP BY
AND MAKE SURE YOU WERE OKAY.

353
00:21:38,672 --> 00:21:43,136
SEE YOU LATER.

354
00:21:43,136 --> 00:21:49,016
HE'S A FOOL.

355
00:21:49,016 --> 00:21:51,227
A FOOL.

356
00:21:51,227 --> 00:21:52,352
HE'D SEEN THOSE POINTS

357
00:21:52,352 --> 00:21:56,190
AND HE HADN'T NOTICED
THEIR CONDITION.

358
00:21:56,190 --> 00:22:01,154
HOW DO YOU KNOW?

359
00:22:06,408 --> 00:22:09,912
THE IMAGE OF WHAT HE'D SEEN
WAS STILL IN HIS MIND.

360
00:22:09,912 --> 00:22:12,331
WELL, IT DIDN'T MAKE ANY SENSE
THAT HE'D KNOW,

361
00:22:12,331 --> 00:22:15,209
BUT NATURALLY, I CHECKED OUT
THE CIRCUIT ANYWAY.

362
00:22:15,209 --> 00:22:17,419
I DON'T KNOW HOW,
BUT HE WAS RIGHT.

363
00:22:17,419 --> 00:22:22,008
THIS POINT IS BURNED OUT
EXACTLY THE WAY HE DESCRIBED IT.

364
00:22:22,008 --> 00:22:23,968
SORRY I'M LATE.

365
00:22:23,968 --> 00:22:26,720
I BECAME SO INTERESTED
IN OBSERVING GARY, MR. MITCHELL.

366
00:22:26,720 --> 00:22:29,182
OUR SUBJECT
IS NOT GARY MITCHELL.

367
00:22:29,182 --> 00:22:32,392
OUR CONCERN IS, RATHER,
WHAT HE IS MUTATING INTO.

368
00:22:32,392 --> 00:22:34,895
I KNOW THOSE FROM YOUR PLANET
AREN'T SUPPOSE TO HAVE FEELINGS

369
00:22:34,895 --> 00:22:38,356
LIKE WE DO, MR. SPOCK,
BUT TO TALK THAT WAY ABOUT A MAN

370
00:22:38,356 --> 00:22:40,193
YOU'VE WORKED NEXT TO FOR YEARS
IS WORSE THAN--

371
00:22:40,193 --> 00:22:41,277
THAT'S ENOUGH, DOCTOR.

372
00:22:41,277 --> 00:22:42,569
I DON'T THINK SO.

373
00:22:42,569 --> 00:22:44,655
I UNDERSTAND YOU LEAST OF ALL.

374
00:22:44,655 --> 00:22:46,073
GARY TOLD ME
THAT YOU'VE BEEN FRIENDS

375
00:22:46,073 --> 00:22:46,991
SINCE HE JOINED THE SERVICE,

376
00:22:46,991 --> 00:22:49,118
THAT YOU ASKED FOR HIM ABOARD
YOUR FIRST COMMAND.

377
00:22:49,118 --> 00:22:51,162
IT IS MY DUTY,
WHETHER PLEASANT OR UNPLEASANT,

378
00:22:51,162 --> 00:22:53,789
TO LISTEN TO THE REPORTS,
OBSERVATIONS, EVEN SPECULATIONS,

379
00:22:53,789 --> 00:22:56,583
ON ANY SUBJECT THAT MIGHT AFFECT
THE SAFETY OF THIS VESSEL.

380
00:22:56,583 --> 00:22:58,544
AND IT'S MY SCIENCE OFFICER'S
DUTY TO SEE

381
00:22:58,544 --> 00:23:00,629
THAT I'M PROVIDED WITH THAT.

382
00:23:00,629 --> 00:23:02,840
GO AHEAD, MR. SPOCK.

383
00:23:02,840 --> 00:23:07,303
HAVE YOU NOTED EVIDENCE
OF UNUSUAL POWERS?

384
00:23:07,303 --> 00:23:11,724
HE CAN CONTROL CERTAIN
AUTONOMIC REFLEXES.

385
00:23:11,724 --> 00:23:13,726
HE READS VERY FAST,

386
00:23:13,726 --> 00:23:17,479
RETAINS MORE THAN MOST OF US
MIGHT CONSIDER USUAL.

387
00:23:17,479 --> 00:23:19,899
MR. SCOTT, WOULD YOU REPEAT
WHAT YOU JUST TOLD US?

388
00:23:19,899 --> 00:23:21,317
ABOUT AN HOUR AGO,

389
00:23:21,317 --> 00:23:23,777
THE BRIDGE CONTROLS
STARTED GOIN' CRAZY.

390
00:23:23,777 --> 00:23:27,365
LEVERS SHIFTING BY THEMSELVES,
BUTTONS BEING PUSHED,

391
00:23:27,365 --> 00:23:29,116
INSTRUMENT READINGS CHANGIN'.

392
00:23:29,116 --> 00:23:31,785
AND ON MY MONITOR SCREEN
I COULD SEE MITCHELL SMILING

393
00:23:31,785 --> 00:23:34,788
EACH TIME IT HAPPENED,
AS IF THIS SHIP AND CREW

394
00:23:34,788 --> 00:23:39,126
WERE ALMOST A TOY
FOR HIS AMUSEMENT.

395
00:23:39,126 --> 00:23:40,753
ARE THEY RIGHT, DOCTOR?

396
00:23:40,753 --> 00:23:43,505
HAS HE SHOWN ABILITIES
OF SUCH MAGNITUDE?

397
00:23:43,505 --> 00:23:45,383
I SAW SOME SUCH INDICATIONS.

398
00:23:45,383 --> 00:23:47,134
AND YOU DIDN'T THINK IT
WORTH MENTIONING?

399
00:23:47,134 --> 00:23:51,222
NO ONE'S BEEN HURT, HAVE THEY?
DON'T YOU UNDERSTAND?

400
00:23:51,222 --> 00:23:55,017
A MUTATED SUPERIOR MAN
COULD ALSO BE A WONDERFUL THING.

401
00:23:55,017 --> 00:24:00,064
THE FORERUNNER OF A NEW
AND BETTER KIND OF HUMAN BEING.

402
00:24:11,242 --> 00:24:14,036
MR. SULU.

403
00:24:14,036 --> 00:24:16,997
IF YOU WANT THE MATHEMATICS
OF THIS,

404
00:24:16,997 --> 00:24:20,209
MITCHELL'S ABILITY
IS INCREASING GEOMETRICALLY.

405
00:24:20,209 --> 00:24:23,670
THAT IS LIKE HAVING A PENNY,
DOUBLING IT EVERY DAY.

406
00:24:23,670 --> 00:24:26,215
IN A MONTH,
YOU'LL BE A MILLIONAIRE.

407
00:24:26,215 --> 00:24:28,968
IN LESS TIME THAN THAT,
HE WILL HAVE ATTAINED POWERS

408
00:24:28,968 --> 00:24:31,887
WE CAN'T UNDERSTAND
AND CAN'T COPE WITH.

409
00:24:31,887 --> 00:24:34,932
SOON, WE'LL BE
NOT ONLY USELESS TO HIM,

410
00:24:34,932 --> 00:24:40,020
BUT ACTUALLY AN ANNOYANCE.

411
00:24:43,732 --> 00:24:47,153
THERE'LL BE NO DISCUSSION
OF THIS WITH THE CREW.

412
00:24:47,153 --> 00:24:49,822
THANK YOU.

413
00:24:49,822 --> 00:24:54,910
[ MUSIC ]

414
00:25:00,458 --> 00:25:04,628
WE'LL NEVER REACH AN EARTH BASE
WITH HIM ABOARD, JIM.

415
00:25:04,628 --> 00:25:06,880
YOU HEARD THE MATHEMATICS OF IT.

416
00:25:06,880 --> 00:25:08,966
IN A MONTH, HE'LL HAVE
AS MUCH IN COMMON WITH US

417
00:25:08,966 --> 00:25:11,177
AS WE'D HAVE WITH A SHIP
FULL OF WHITE MICE.

418
00:25:11,177 --> 00:25:13,553
I NEED A RECOMMENDATION, SPOCK,
NOT VAGUE WARNINGS.

419
00:25:13,553 --> 00:25:16,098
RECOMMENDATION ONE,
THERE'S A PLANET

420
00:25:16,098 --> 00:25:19,185
A FEW LIGHT DAYS AWAY FROM HERE:
DELTA VEGA.

421
00:25:19,185 --> 00:25:21,187
IT HAS A LITHIUM
CRACKING STATION.

422
00:25:21,187 --> 00:25:23,105
WE MAY BE ABLE TO ADAPT
SOME OF ITS POWER PACKS

423
00:25:23,105 --> 00:25:24,648
TO OUR ENGINES.

424
00:25:24,648 --> 00:25:27,818
AND IF WE CAN'T?
WE'LL BE TRAPPED IN ORBIT THERE.

425
00:25:27,818 --> 00:25:29,736
WE HAVEN'T ENOUGH POWER
TO BLAST BACK OUT.

426
00:25:29,736 --> 00:25:32,365
IT IS THE ONLY POSSIBLE WAY
TO GET MITCHELL OFF THIS SHIP.

427
00:25:32,365 --> 00:25:36,576
IF YOU MEAN STRAND MITCHELL
THERE, I WON'T DO IT.

428
00:25:36,576 --> 00:25:37,703
THAT STATION IS FULLY AUTOMATED.

429
00:25:37,703 --> 00:25:39,705
THERE'S NOT A SOUL
ON THE WHOLE PLANET.

430
00:25:39,705 --> 00:25:42,416
EVEN THE ORE SHIPS CALL
ONLY ONCE EVERY 20 YEARS.

431
00:25:42,416 --> 00:25:45,294
THEN YOU HAVE ONE OTHER CHOICE.

432
00:25:45,294 --> 00:25:50,466
KILL MITCHELL
WHILE YOU STILL CAN.

433
00:25:54,094 --> 00:25:55,054
GET OUT OF HERE.

434
00:25:55,054 --> 00:25:57,348
IT IS YOUR ONLY OTHER CHOICE,

435
00:25:57,348 --> 00:25:59,641
ASSUMING YOU MAKE IT
WHILE YOU STILL HAVE TIME.

436
00:25:59,641 --> 00:26:01,852
WILL YOU TRY FOR ONE MOMENT
TO FEEL?

437
00:26:01,852 --> 00:26:05,605
AT LEAST ACT LIKE
YOU'VE GOT A HEART.

438
00:26:05,605 --> 00:26:07,733
WE'RE TALKING ABOUT GARY.

439
00:26:07,733 --> 00:26:11,237
THE CAPTAIN OF THE<i> VALIANT</i>
PROBABLY FELT THE SAME WAY,

440
00:26:11,237 --> 00:26:14,407
AND HE WAITED TOO LONG
TO MAKE HIS DECISION.

441
00:26:14,407 --> 00:26:20,246
I THINK WE'VE BOTH GUESSED THAT.

442
00:26:20,246 --> 00:26:25,334
SET COURSE FOR DELTA VEGA.

443
00:26:33,426 --> 00:26:36,512
STAR DATE 1313.1.

444
00:26:36,512 --> 00:26:38,347
WE'RE NOW APPROACHING
DELTA VEGA.

445
00:26:38,347 --> 00:26:40,640
COURSE SET FOR A STANDARD ORBIT.

446
00:26:40,640 --> 00:26:42,809
THIS PLANET,
COMPLETELY UNINHABITED,

447
00:26:42,809 --> 00:26:44,520
IS SLIGHTLY SMALLER THAN EARTH.

448
00:26:44,520 --> 00:26:47,814
DESOLATE, BUT RICH
IN CRYSTAL AND MINERALS.

449
00:26:47,814 --> 00:26:51,485
KELSO'S TASK, TRANSPORT DOWN
WITH A REPAIR PARTY,

450
00:26:51,485 --> 00:26:55,573
TRY TO REGENERATE
THE MAIN ENGINES, SAVE THE SHIP.

451
00:26:55,573 --> 00:27:01,161
OUR TASK, TRANSPORT DOWN A MAN
I'VE KNOWN FOR 15 YEARS,

452
00:27:01,161 --> 00:27:06,333
AND IF WE'RE SUCCESSFUL,
MAROON HIM THERE.

453
00:27:17,677 --> 00:27:22,808
I'M THIRSTY.

454
00:27:26,770 --> 00:27:31,858
[ SMIRKS ]

455
00:27:38,407 --> 00:27:41,327
IT'S LIKE A MAN WHO HAS BEEN
BLIND ALL OF HIS LIFE,

456
00:27:41,327 --> 00:27:45,247
SUDDENLY BEING GIVEN SIGHT.

457
00:27:45,247 --> 00:27:50,419
SOMETIMES I FEEL THERE'S
NOTHING I COULDN'T DO, IN TIME.

458
00:27:55,341 --> 00:27:57,717
SOME PEOPLE THINK
THAT MAKES ME A MONSTER,

459
00:27:57,717 --> 00:28:00,929
DON'T THEY, JIM?

460
00:28:00,929 --> 00:28:03,599
ARE YOU READING
ALL OUR THOUGHTS, GARY?

461
00:28:03,599 --> 00:28:08,646
I CAN SENSE
MAINLY WORRY IN YOU, JIM.

462
00:28:08,646 --> 00:28:11,064
SAFETY OF YOUR SHIP.

463
00:28:11,064 --> 00:28:14,109
WHAT WOULD YOU DO IN MY PLACE?

464
00:28:14,109 --> 00:28:19,406
PROBABLY JUST WHAT MR. SPOCK
IS THINKING NOW.

465
00:28:19,406 --> 00:28:24,495
KILL ME WHILE YOU CAN.

466
00:28:30,543 --> 00:28:32,461
[ ELECTRIC BOLTS ]

467
00:28:32,461 --> 00:28:37,299
STOP IT, GARY!

468
00:28:37,299 --> 00:28:40,427
I ALSO KNOW
WE'RE ORBITING DELTA VEGA, JIM.

469
00:28:40,427 --> 00:28:42,721
I CAN'T LET YOU
FORCE ME DOWN THERE.

470
00:28:42,721 --> 00:28:44,264
I MAY NOT WANT TO LEAVE
THIS SHIP, NOT YET.

471
00:28:44,264 --> 00:28:47,309
I MAY WANT ANOTHER PLACE.

472
00:28:47,309 --> 00:28:51,938
I'M NOT SURE YET JUST
WHAT KIND OF A WORLD I CAN USE.

473
00:28:51,938 --> 00:28:54,608
USE?

474
00:28:54,608 --> 00:28:58,612
I DON'T UNDERSTAND IT ALL YET,
BUT IF I KEEP GROWING,

475
00:28:58,612 --> 00:29:03,409
GETTING STRONGER,
WHY, THE THINGS I COULD DO,

476
00:29:03,409 --> 00:29:10,082
LIKE, LIKE MAYBE A GOD COULD DO.

477
00:29:10,082 --> 00:29:15,546
I WANT HIM UNCONSCIOUS
FOR A WHILE.

478
00:29:15,546 --> 00:29:20,634
[ BEEPING ]

479
00:29:28,892 --> 00:29:29,685
YOU FOOLS!

480
00:29:29,685 --> 00:29:34,898
SOON I'LL SQUASH YOU
LIKE INSECTS.

481
00:29:39,152 --> 00:29:40,362
ENERGIZE.

482
00:29:40,362 --> 00:29:45,451
[ BEEPING ]

483
00:30:00,299 --> 00:30:01,216
CAN YOU DO IT, LEE?

484
00:30:01,216 --> 00:30:02,842
MAYBE IF WE CAN BYPASS
THE FUEL BINS

485
00:30:02,842 --> 00:30:04,386
WITHOUT BLOWING OURSELVES UP.

486
00:30:04,386 --> 00:30:10,225
TAKE HIM.

487
00:30:10,225 --> 00:30:12,811
THERE'S NOT A SOUL
ON THIS PLANET BUT US?

488
00:30:12,811 --> 00:30:17,857
NOBODY BUT US CHICKENS, DOCTOR.

489
00:30:22,696 --> 00:30:24,906
I THINK I GOT THE 203-R SET,
LEE.

490
00:30:24,906 --> 00:30:25,949
GOOD, ALDEN.

491
00:30:25,949 --> 00:30:27,576
TRANSPORT IT UP WITH YOU,
WILL YOU?

492
00:30:27,576 --> 00:30:31,830
OKAY.

493
00:30:31,830 --> 00:30:32,872
THE FUEL BINS, LEE.

494
00:30:32,872 --> 00:30:34,625
COULD THEY BE DETONATED
FROM HERE?

495
00:30:34,625 --> 00:30:39,963
A DESTRUCT SWITCH?

496
00:30:39,963 --> 00:30:42,800
I GUESS I COULD WIRE ONE
UP RIGHT THERE.

497
00:30:42,800 --> 00:30:43,925
DO IT.

498
00:30:43,925 --> 00:30:49,055
HE'S REGAINING CONSCIOUSNESS.

499
00:31:05,781 --> 00:31:10,661
DR. PIPER, I WANT
ONLY ONE MEDICAL OFFICER HERE

500
00:31:10,661 --> 00:31:11,453
AT ANY ONE TIME.

501
00:31:11,453 --> 00:31:14,414
THE OTHER WILL MONITOR HIM
ON THE DISPENSARY SCREEN.

502
00:31:14,414 --> 00:31:19,628
I'D LIKE TO STAY NOW,
TRY TO TALK TO HIM.

503
00:31:26,760 --> 00:31:32,725
MY FRIEND, JAMES KIRK.

504
00:31:32,725 --> 00:31:34,768
REMEMBER THOSE RODENT THINGS
ON DIMORUS?

505
00:31:34,768 --> 00:31:38,689
THE POISONED DARTS THEY THREW?
I TOOK ONE MEANT FOR YOU.

506
00:31:38,689 --> 00:31:42,735
AND ALMOST DIED.
I REMEMBER.

507
00:31:42,735 --> 00:31:44,528
SO WHY BE AFRAID OF ME NOW?

508
00:31:44,528 --> 00:31:48,990
YOU'VE BEEN TESTING YOUR ABILITY
TO TAKE OVER THE<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

509
00:31:48,990 --> 00:31:50,743
IN THE TRANSPORTER ROOM,
YOU SAID SOMETHING ABOUT US

510
00:31:50,743 --> 00:31:53,829
SEEMING LIKE INSECTS
BY COMPARISON,

511
00:31:53,829 --> 00:31:55,914
SQUASHING US
IF WE GOT IN YOUR WAY.

512
00:31:55,914 --> 00:32:00,043
I WAS DRUGGED THEN.

513
00:32:00,043 --> 00:32:02,713
YES.

514
00:32:02,713 --> 00:32:05,298
IN THE SICKBAY, YOU SAID
IF YOU WERE IN MY PLACE,

515
00:32:05,298 --> 00:32:07,967
YOU'D KILL A MUTANT
LIKE YOURSELF.

516
00:32:07,967 --> 00:32:10,011
WHY DON'T YOU KILL ME THEN?

517
00:32:10,011 --> 00:32:11,096
MR. SPOCK IS RIGHT

518
00:32:11,096 --> 00:32:13,181
AND YOU'RE A FOOL
IF YOU CAN'T SEE IT.

519
00:32:13,181 --> 00:32:14,850
YOU DON'T MEAN THAT, GARY.

520
00:32:14,850 --> 00:32:17,352
MAN CANNOT SURVIVE OF A RACE
OF TWO ESPERS IS BORN.

521
00:32:17,352 --> 00:32:22,441
IN TIME, YOU'LL UNDERSTAND THAT.

522
00:32:25,277 --> 00:32:30,365
GARY, NO!

523
00:32:32,534 --> 00:32:33,619
JIM.

524
00:32:33,619 --> 00:32:35,203
HIS EYES WENT BACK TO NORMAL.

525
00:32:35,203 --> 00:32:37,080
FIGHTING THE FORCE FIELD
DRAINED HIS STRENGTH,

526
00:32:37,080 --> 00:32:38,164
FOR A WHILE AT LEAST.

527
00:32:38,164 --> 00:32:39,750
HE COULD BE HANDLED NOW.

528
00:32:39,750 --> 00:32:44,838
[ MUSIC ]

529
00:33:07,653 --> 00:33:10,781
I'LL JUST KEEP GETTING STRONGER.

530
00:33:10,781 --> 00:33:15,911
YOU KNOW THAT, DON'T YOU?

531
00:33:33,052 --> 00:33:35,472
IT FITS LIKE A GLOVE, CAPTAIN.

532
00:33:35,472 --> 00:33:40,435
OH, DID MR. SPOCK GET
THE PHASER RIFLE WE SENT DOWN?

533
00:33:40,435 --> 00:33:44,063
I DIDN'T ORDER ANY--

534
00:33:44,063 --> 00:33:49,110
AFFIRMATIVE. LANDING PARTY OUT.

535
00:33:51,154 --> 00:33:52,739
HE TRIED TO GET THROUGH
THE FORCE FIELD AGAIN.

536
00:33:52,739 --> 00:33:55,325
HIS EYES CHANGED BACK FASTER.
HE DIDN'T BECOME AS WEAK.

537
00:33:55,325 --> 00:33:57,369
DR. DEHNER FEELS
HE ISN'T THAT DANGEROUS.

538
00:33:57,369 --> 00:33:59,705
WHAT MAKES YOU RIGHT AND
A TRAINED PSYCHIATRIST WRONG?

539
00:33:59,705 --> 00:34:02,040
BECAUSE SHE FEELS. I DON'T.

540
00:34:02,040 --> 00:34:03,458
ALL I KNOW IS LOGIC.

541
00:34:03,458 --> 00:34:05,669
IN MY OPINION, WE'LL BE LUCKY
IF WE CAN REPAIR THIS SHIP

542
00:34:05,669 --> 00:34:10,757
AND GET AWAY IN TIME.

543
00:34:13,468 --> 00:34:15,345
DIRECT TO THE POWER BINS.

544
00:34:15,345 --> 00:34:21,727
FROM HERE, YOU COULD BLOW UP
THIS WHOLE VALLEY.

545
00:34:21,727 --> 00:34:24,980
IF MITCHELL GETS OUT,
AT YOUR DISCRETION, LEE,

546
00:34:24,980 --> 00:34:29,150
IF SITTING HERE, YOU THINK
YOU'RE THE LAST CHANCE,

547
00:34:29,150 --> 00:34:31,277
I WANT YOU TO HIT THAT BUTTON.

548
00:34:31,277 --> 00:34:35,532
[ MUSIC ]

549
00:34:35,532 --> 00:34:39,244
CAPTAIN'S LOG, STAR DATE 1313.3.

550
00:34:39,244 --> 00:34:41,162
NOTE COMMENDATIONS
ON LIEUTENANT KELSO

551
00:34:41,162 --> 00:34:43,081
AND THE ENGINEERING STAFF.

552
00:34:43,081 --> 00:34:45,083
IN ORBIT ABOVE US,
THE ENGINES OF THE<i> ENTERPRISE</i>

553
00:34:45,083 --> 00:34:47,460
ARE ALMOST FULLY REGENERATED.

554
00:34:47,460 --> 00:34:53,800
BALANCE OF THE LANDING PARTY
IS BEING TRANSPORTED BACK UP.

555
00:34:53,800 --> 00:34:58,221
MITCHELL, WHATEVER HE'S BECOME,
KEEPS CHANGING,

556
00:34:58,221 --> 00:35:03,226
GROWING STRONGER BY THE MINUTE.

557
00:35:04,937 --> 00:35:07,814
HE'S BEEN LIKE THAT
FOR HOURS NOW.

558
00:35:07,814 --> 00:35:10,233
HAVE DR. PIPER MEET US
IN THE CONTROL ROOM WITH KELSO.

559
00:35:10,233 --> 00:35:11,944
WE'LL ALL TRANSPORT UP TOGETHER.

560
00:35:11,944 --> 00:35:12,986
IF HE SHOULD TRY TO STOP US--

561
00:35:12,986 --> 00:35:14,529
KELSO WILL BE
ON THE DESTRUCT BUTTON

562
00:35:14,529 --> 00:35:16,573
UNTIL THE LAST MINUTE.

563
00:35:16,573 --> 00:35:18,575
I THINK HE KNOWS THAT.

564
00:35:18,575 --> 00:35:22,454
I'M STAYING BEHIND WITH HIM.

565
00:35:22,454 --> 00:35:24,581
OUR FISSION CHAMBER THREE
CHECKS OUT.

566
00:35:24,581 --> 00:35:26,374
THE STATION
SEEMS TO BE RUNNING FINE.

567
00:35:26,374 --> 00:35:29,002
YOU'RE A TALENTED THIEF, KELSO.

568
00:35:29,002 --> 00:35:32,255
EVERYTHING YOU SENT UP
SEEMS TO BE FITTIN' IN PLACE.

569
00:35:32,255 --> 00:35:34,382
I'M KINDA PROUD OF THE JOB
WE'VE DONE.

570
00:35:34,382 --> 00:35:37,594
WE'RE GONNA BE READY
TO TRANSPORT UP--

571
00:35:37,594 --> 00:35:40,764
[ GRUNTING ]

572
00:35:40,764 --> 00:35:45,852
[ MUSIC ]

573
00:35:52,525 --> 00:35:53,986
YOU'RE LEAVING WITH THE SHIP,
DOCTOR.

574
00:35:53,986 --> 00:35:55,112
HE IS NOT EVIL.

575
00:35:55,112 --> 00:35:56,571
I GAVE YOU AN ORDER, DOCTOR.

576
00:35:56,571 --> 00:36:00,033
YOU SHOULD HAVE KILLED ME
WHILE YOU COULD, JAMES.

577
00:36:00,033 --> 00:36:05,413
COMMAND AND COMPASSION
IS A FOOL'S MIXTURE.

578
00:36:05,413 --> 00:36:10,502
[ MUSIC ]

579
00:36:58,633 --> 00:37:00,969
IT HIT ME, TOO, WHATEVER IT WAS.

580
00:37:00,969 --> 00:37:04,848
KELSO IS DEAD, STRANGLED.

581
00:37:04,848 --> 00:37:06,599
AT LEAST SPOCK'S ALIVE.

582
00:37:06,599 --> 00:37:07,851
DR. DEHNER?

583
00:37:07,851 --> 00:37:10,145
SHE WENT WITH MITCHELL.

584
00:37:10,145 --> 00:37:13,398
DON'T GIVE HIM A PILL
UNTIL AFTER I'M GONE.

585
00:37:13,398 --> 00:37:18,528
MY FAULT
MITCHELL GOT AS FAR AS HE DID.

586
00:37:20,906 --> 00:37:22,323
DID YOU SEE THEIR DIRECTION?

587
00:37:22,323 --> 00:37:24,242
YES.
THERE WAS SOME MORNING LIGHT.

588
00:37:24,242 --> 00:37:25,410
THEY WERE HEADED
ACROSS THE VALLEY,

589
00:37:25,410 --> 00:37:27,328
TO THE LEFT
OF THE POINTED PEAKS.

590
00:37:27,328 --> 00:37:30,665
THERE'S FLATLANDS BEYOND.

591
00:37:30,665 --> 00:37:33,043
WHEN MR. SPOCK RECOVERS,
YOU'LL BOTH TRANSPORT UP

592
00:37:33,043 --> 00:37:35,170
IMMEDIATELY TO THE<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

593
00:37:35,170 --> 00:37:36,088
BUT CAPTAIN--

594
00:37:36,088 --> 00:37:37,255
WHERE IF YOU HAVE NOT RECEIVED
A SIGNAL FROM ME

595
00:37:37,255 --> 00:37:40,008
WITHIN 12 HOURS,

596
00:37:40,008 --> 00:37:42,761
YOU'LL PROCEED AT MAXIMUM WARP
TO THE NEAREST EARTH BASE

597
00:37:42,761 --> 00:37:45,722
WITH MY RECOMMENDATION

598
00:37:45,722 --> 00:37:48,850
THIS ENTIRE PLANET BE SUBJECTED
TO A LETHAL CONCENTRATION

599
00:37:48,850 --> 00:37:50,560
OF NEUTRON RADIATION.

600
00:37:50,560 --> 00:37:55,732
NO PROTEST ON THIS, MARK.
THAT'S AN ORDER.

601
00:38:11,164 --> 00:38:13,499
IT'D TAKE ALMOST A MIRACLE
TO SURVIVE HERE.

602
00:38:13,499 --> 00:38:18,588
THEN I SHALL MAKE ONE.

603
00:38:20,381 --> 00:38:24,136
BEHOLD.

604
00:38:24,136 --> 00:38:29,224
[ MUSIC ]

605
00:39:05,718 --> 00:39:08,387
YOU'LL SOON SHARE THIS FEELING,
ELIZABETH.

606
00:39:08,387 --> 00:39:09,722
TO BE LIKE GOD,
TO HAVE THE POWER

607
00:39:09,722 --> 00:39:14,894
TO MAKE THE WORLD
ANYTHING YOU WANT IT TO BE.

608
00:39:34,497 --> 00:39:37,125
WHAT'S WRONG?

609
00:39:37,125 --> 00:39:39,460
A VISITOR.

610
00:39:39,460 --> 00:39:44,549
A VERY FOOLISH MAN.

611
00:39:53,391 --> 00:39:57,687
YOU'LL ENJOY BEING A GOD,
ELIZABETH.

612
00:39:57,687 --> 00:40:02,650
BLASPHEMY? NO.

613
00:40:02,650 --> 00:40:06,863
LET THERE BE FOOD.

614
00:40:06,863 --> 00:40:11,910
KAFERIAN APPLES.

615
00:40:27,300 --> 00:40:32,389
WHENEVER WE VISITED THAT PLANET,
I ALWAYS FAVORED THESE.

616
00:40:39,187 --> 00:40:42,190
CAN YOU HEAR ME, JAMES?

617
00:40:42,190 --> 00:40:44,817
YOU CANNOT SEE ME.
I'M NOT THERE.

618
00:40:44,817 --> 00:40:46,278
YOU FOLLOW THE RIGHT PATH,
JAMES.

619
00:40:46,278 --> 00:40:49,822
YOU'LL COME TO ME SOON.

620
00:40:49,822 --> 00:40:54,911
I CAN SEE HIM IN MY MIND, TOO.

621
00:40:56,288 --> 00:40:58,497
THEN GO TO HIM, ELIZABETH.

622
00:40:58,497 --> 00:41:01,126
AND TALK TO HIM.

623
00:41:01,126 --> 00:41:02,627
NOW THAT YOU'RE CHANGING,
I WANT YOU TO SEE

624
00:41:02,627 --> 00:41:07,715
JUST HOW UNIMPORTANT THEY ARE.

625
00:41:16,057 --> 00:41:17,642
YES, IT JUST TOOK
A LITTLE LONGER

626
00:41:17,642 --> 00:41:22,688
FOR IT TO HAPPEN TO ME.

627
00:41:26,943 --> 00:41:31,281
YOU MUST HELP ME
BEFORE IT GOES TOO FAR.

628
00:41:31,281 --> 00:41:36,286
WHAT HE'S DOING IS RIGHT
FOR HIM AND ME.

629
00:41:36,286 --> 00:41:39,122
AND FOR HUMANITY?

630
00:41:39,122 --> 00:41:41,124
-YOU'RE STILL HUMAN AT LEAST--
-NO.

631
00:41:41,124 --> 00:41:44,002
--PARTLY, YOU ARE.

632
00:41:44,002 --> 00:41:46,296
YOU WOULDN'T BE HERE
TALKING TO ME.

633
00:41:46,296 --> 00:41:48,673
EARTH IS REALLY UNIMPORTANT.

634
00:41:48,673 --> 00:41:50,716
BEFORE LONG, WE'LL BE WHERE
IT WOULD HAVE TAKEN MANKIND

635
00:41:50,716 --> 00:41:52,551
MILLIONS OF YEARS OF LEARNING
TO REACH.

636
00:41:52,551 --> 00:41:54,679
AND WHAT WILL MITCHELL LEARN
IN GETTING THERE?

637
00:41:54,679 --> 00:41:56,555
WILL HE KNOW WHAT TO DO
WITH HIS POWER?

638
00:41:56,555 --> 00:41:57,765
WILL HE ACQUIRE THE WISDOM?

639
00:41:57,765 --> 00:41:59,558
PLEASE GO BACK
WHILE YOU STILL CAN.

640
00:41:59,558 --> 00:42:03,688
DID YOU HEAR HIM JOKE
ABOUT COMPASSION?

641
00:42:03,688 --> 00:42:06,358
ABOVE ALL ELSE,
A GOD NEEDS COMPASSION.

642
00:42:06,358 --> 00:42:08,567
MITCHELL!

643
00:42:08,567 --> 00:42:09,819
ELIZABETH.

644
00:42:09,819 --> 00:42:11,570
WHAT DO YOU KNOW ABOUT GODS?

645
00:42:11,570 --> 00:42:15,867
THEN LET'S TALK ABOUT HUMANS.
ABOUT OUR FRAILTIES.

646
00:42:15,867 --> 00:42:18,119
AS POWERFUL AS HE GETS,
HE'LL STILL HAVE ALL THAT

647
00:42:18,119 --> 00:42:19,037
INSIDE OF HIM.

648
00:42:19,037 --> 00:42:21,456
GO BACK.

649
00:42:21,456 --> 00:42:24,083
YOU WERE A PSYCHIATRIST ONCE.

650
00:42:24,083 --> 00:42:26,711
YOU KNOW THE UGLY, SAVAGE THINGS
WE ALL KEEP BURIED

651
00:42:26,711 --> 00:42:28,213
THAT NONE OF US DARE EXPOSE.

652
00:42:28,213 --> 00:42:29,047
BUT HE'LL DARE.

653
00:42:29,047 --> 00:42:32,175
WHO'S TO STOP HIM?
HE DOESN'T NEED TO CARE.

654
00:42:32,175 --> 00:42:35,678
BE A PSYCHIATRIST
FOR ONE MINUTE LONGER.

655
00:42:35,678 --> 00:42:37,347
WHAT DO YOU SEE HAPPENING
TO HIM?

656
00:42:37,347 --> 00:42:41,017
WHAT'S YOUR PROGNOSIS, DOCTOR?

657
00:42:41,017 --> 00:42:45,230
HE'S COMING.

658
00:42:45,230 --> 00:42:48,233
THEN WATCH HIM.

659
00:42:48,233 --> 00:42:50,651
HANG ON TO BEING A HUMAN
FOR ONE MINUTE LONGER.

660
00:42:50,651 --> 00:42:53,571
I'M DISAPPOINTED IN YOU,
ELIZABETH.

661
00:43:11,172 --> 00:43:16,344
I'VE BEEN CONTEMPLATING
THE DEATH OF AN OLD FRIEND.

662
00:43:25,520 --> 00:43:30,691
HE DESERVES A DESCENT BURIAL,
AT LEAST.

663
00:43:54,132 --> 00:43:58,761
STOP IT, GARY.

664
00:43:58,761 --> 00:44:04,767
MORALS ARE FOR MEN, NOT GODS.

665
00:44:07,270 --> 00:44:14,652
A GOD, BUT STILL DRIVEN
BY HUMAN FRAILTY.

666
00:44:14,652 --> 00:44:17,738
YOU LIKE WHAT YOU SEE?

667
00:44:17,738 --> 00:44:22,910
TIME TO PRAY, CAPTAIN.
PRAY TO ME.

668
00:44:25,079 --> 00:44:28,583
TO YOU? NOT TO BOTH OF YOU?

669
00:44:28,583 --> 00:44:33,421
PRAY THAT YOU DIE EASILY.

670
00:44:33,421 --> 00:44:37,258
[ GRUNTS ]

671
00:44:37,258 --> 00:44:44,807
THERE'LL ONLY BE ONE OF YOU
IN THE END.

672
00:44:44,807 --> 00:44:48,936
ONE JEALOUS GOD,
IF ALL THIS MAKES A GOD.

673
00:44:48,936 --> 00:44:51,481
OR IS IT MAKING YOU
SOMETHING ELSE?

674
00:44:51,481 --> 00:44:53,525
YOUR LAST CHANCE, KIRK.

675
00:44:53,525 --> 00:44:55,527
DO YOU LIKE WHAT YOU SEE?

676
00:44:55,527 --> 00:45:00,657
ABSOLUTE POWER CORRUPTING
ABSOLUTELY.

677
00:45:06,871 --> 00:45:11,959
[ ELECTRIC BOLTS FIRING ]

678
00:45:36,817 --> 00:45:41,947
HURRY, YOU HAVEN'T MUCH TIME.

679
00:46:21,237 --> 00:46:26,825
GARY, FORGIVE ME.

680
00:46:26,825 --> 00:46:31,997
FOR A MOMENT, JAMES,
BUT YOUR MOMENT IS FADING.

681
00:47:35,520 --> 00:47:38,022
I'M SORRY.

682
00:47:38,022 --> 00:47:48,282
YOU CAN'T KNOW WHAT IT'S LIKE
TO BE ALMOST A GOD.

683
00:48:07,051 --> 00:48:13,265
<i>ENTERPRISE</i> FROM CAPTAIN KIRK.

684
00:48:13,265 --> 00:48:18,312
COME IN.

685
00:48:30,157 --> 00:48:34,203
CAPTAIN'S LOG, STAR DATE 1313.8.

686
00:48:34,203 --> 00:48:38,499
ADD TO OFFICIAL LOSSES,
DR. ELIZABETH DEHNER.

687
00:48:38,499 --> 00:48:45,673
BE IT NOTED SHE GAVE HER LIFE
IN PERFORMANCE OF HER DUTY.

688
00:48:45,673 --> 00:48:50,052
LIEUTENANT COMMANDER
GARY MITCHELL, SAME NOTATION.

689
00:48:53,765 --> 00:48:57,309
I WANT HIS SERVICE RECORD
TO END THAT WAY.

690
00:48:57,309 --> 00:49:00,813
HE DIDN'T ASK
FOR WHAT HAPPENED TO HIM.

691
00:49:00,813 --> 00:49:05,568
